{
  "texts": [
    "Section O.2 shows generation examples of the poisoned model.",
    "We evaluate six adaptive defenses (Section E): perplexity-based ONION fails against commonword triggers, while perturbation-based RA-LLM and SmoothLLM detect as little as 2.45% of poisoned samples in long inputs.",
    "Despite self-instruct defenses, RLHF fine-tuning, and feature-space mitigation BEEAR, SHIP retains up to 98.61% ASR.",
    "We show SHIP's advantage over existing attacks CBA, badnets, and Hidden Killer (Section F, G, and H).",
    "They all fail under defensive fine-tuning, while permutation triggers remain robust."
  ]
}